              are validated before delivery
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Feedback Loops:</strong> Customer feedback helps us 
              improve identification accuracy
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Machine Learning:</strong> Our algorithms continuously 
              learn to improve match rates
            </li>
          </ul>
          
          <p>
            Current accuracy metrics:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>70% visitor identification rate (person-level)</li>
            <li>95%+ email deliverability</li>
            <li>90%+ phone number accuracy</li>
            <li>85%+ job title accuracy</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
          <h2>Data Security</h2>
          <p>
            Cursive employs enterprise-grade security measures:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>SOC 2 Type II certified infrastructure</li>
            <li>256-bit encryption for data at rest and in transit</li>
            <li>Regular security audits and penetration testing</li>
            <li>Role-based access controls</li>
            <li>Automated backup and disaster recovery</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
          <h2>Questions About Data Access?</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about how Cursive accesses and processes data, 
            contact our privacy team at privacy@meetcursive.com or reach out 
            through our <Link href="/contact">contact page</Link>.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Learn more about visitor identification in our guide: 
            <Link href="/what-is-website-visitor-identification">
            What is Website Visitor Identification?</Link>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </>
  );
}

