                <th>Accuracy</th>
                <th>Data Level</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Basic IP Lookup</td>
                <td>30-40%</td>
                <td>85-90%</td>
                <td>Company-level</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Advanced Platforms</td>
                <td>60-70%</td>
                <td>80-85%</td>
                <td>Person-level</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Enterprise Solutions</td>
                <td>70-80%</td>
                <td>90-95%</td>
                <td>Person-level + intent</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          
          <h3>What Affects Match Rates?</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Traffic Source:</strong> Corporate office visitors 
              (80%+ match rate) vs. remote workers (50-60% match rate)
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Geography:</strong> US/UK traffic (70%+ match rate) vs. 
              developing markets (40-50% match rate)
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Company Size:</strong> Enterprise companies (85%+ match rate) 
              vs. SMBs (60% match rate)
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>VPN Usage:</strong> VPN users are harder to identify 
              (30-40% match rate)
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Mobile vs. Desktop:</strong> Desktop traffic (70% match rate) 
              vs. mobile (50% match rate)
            </li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Improving Match Rates</h3>
          <p>You can improve identification accuracy by:</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Installing tracking on all pages (not just homepage)</li>
            <li>Tracking visitors across multiple sessions</li>
            <li>Combining visitor ID with form data</li>
            <li>Using intent data signals</li>
            <li>Implementing progressive profiling</li>
          </ol>
        </section>
        
