          <h3>5. Content Personalization</h3>
          <p>
            Customize website content based on visitor company and industry.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Show industry-specific case studies</li>
            <li>Display relevant product features</li>
            <li>Personalize CTAs and offers</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>6. Pipeline Attribution</h3>
          <p>
            Track which marketing channels drive website visitors that convert 
            to customers.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>See full visitor journey before conversion</li>
            <li>Attribute revenue to marketing touchpoints</li>
            <li>Optimize spend based on visitor quality</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section id="legal">
          <h2>Legal & Compliance Considerations</h2>
          
          <h3>GDPR Compliance (Europe)</h3>
          <p>
            Under GDPR, visitor identification is legal when:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Legitimate Interest:</strong> B2B marketing to business 
              contacts is considered legitimate interest
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Transparency:</strong> Privacy policy discloses data 
              collection practices
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Visitors can opt out of identification
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Data Minimization:</strong> Only collect necessary data
            </li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>CCPA Compliance (California)</h3>
          <p>
            CCPA requires:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Disclosure of data collection in privacy policy</li>
            <li>"Do Not Sell My Personal Information" link</li>
            <li>Honor opt-out requests within 15 days</li>
            <li>Provide data access upon request</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Best Practices for Compliance</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <strong>Update Privacy Policy:</strong> Clearly disclose visitor 
              identification and data sources
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Cookie Banner:</strong> Inform visitors about tracking 
              (though not legally required for B2B in most jurisdictions)
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Opt-Out Form:</strong> Provide easy way for individuals 
              to opt out
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Data Processing Agreement:</strong> Sign DPA with your 
              visitor identification vendor
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Regular Audits:</strong> Review data practices quarterly
            </li>
          </ol>
          
          <h3>B2B vs. B2C Considerations</h3>
          <p>
            Visitor identification is primarily designed for B2B contexts:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>B2B:</strong> Generally legal under "legitimate interest" 
              for business development
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>B2C:</strong> Requires explicit consent in most jurisdictions, 
              making it impractical
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section id="implementation">
          <h2>Implementation Guide</h2>
          
          <h3>Step 1: Choose a Platform</h3>
          <p>
            Evaluate platforms based on:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Match rate (60%+ recommended)</li>
            <li>Data level (person vs. company)</li>
            <li>Integrations with your CRM</li>
            <li>Pricing and contract terms</li>
            <li>Support and training</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Step 2: Install Tracking Pixel</h3>
          <p>
            Most platforms provide a JavaScript snippet to add to your website:
          </p>
          <pre><code>{`<script>
  (function(w,d,s,l,i){
    w[l]=w[l]||[];
    w[l].push({'gtm.start': new Date().getTime(),event:'gtm.js'});
    var f=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],
    j=d.createElement(s),dl=l!='dataLayer'?'&l='+l:'';
    j.async=true;
    j.src='https://platform.example.com/pixel.js?id='+i+dl;
    f.parentNode.insertBefore(j,f);
  })(window,document,'script','dataLayer','YOUR-ID');
</script>`}</code></pre>
          
          <h3>Step 3: Connect Integrations</h3>
          <p>
            Connect your CRM and marketing tools:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <Link href="/integrations/salesforce">Salesforce</Link> - 
              Sync identified visitors to leads/contacts
            </li>
            <li>
              <Link href="/integrations/hubspot">HubSpot</Link> - 
              Create contacts and trigger workflows
            </li>
            <li>
              <Link href="/integrations/slack">Slack</Link> - 
              Get real-time notifications
            </li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Step 4: Set Up Workflows</h3>
          <p>
            Configure automated actions:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Email campaigns to high-intent visitors</li>
            <li>Slack alerts for target accounts</li>
            <li>CRM task creation for sales follow-up</li>
            <li>Retargeting audiences for ad platforms</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Step 5: Train Your Team</h3>
          <p>
            Ensure sales and marketing teams know how to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Access visitor data in the platform</li>
            <li>Interpret behavioral signals</li>
            <li>Prioritize outreach based on intent</li>
            <li>Personalize messaging using visitor context</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Step 6: Measure & Optimize</h3>
          <p>
            Track key metrics:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Identification rate (% of visitors identified)</li>
            <li>Data accuracy (email deliverability, phone accuracy)</li>
            <li>Conversion rate (visitors to leads to customers)</li>
            <li>ROI (revenue attributed to identified visitors)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section id="comparison">
          <h2>Platform Comparison</h2>
